{
  "texts": [
    "Early Stopping is commonly associated with larger numbers of epochs to prevent the network from overfitting and for computational efficiency by avoiding unnecessary epochs.",
    "However, only six publications reported using early stopping.",
    "Regularization also helps prevent the network from overfitting.",
    "Dropout and L2 regularization were the two most common techniques.",
    "Dropout ignores randomly selected neurons during training, which helps prevent overfitting by ensuring that the network does not rely too heavily on any single neuron."
  ]
}